Today's announcements between the Republic of Korea and Japan are seen as a significant development in their cooperation and partnership, as well as their relationship with the United States. President Yoon and Prime Minister Kishida have made historic statements, aiming to create a safer, more secure, and more prosperous future for their people. The United States pledges its support to Japan and South Korea's leaders as they work towards implementing this new understanding. The ultimate goal is to uphold and advance a shared vision of a free and open Indo-Pacific. Strengthening trilateral ties between South Korea, Japan, and the United States is also emphasized, as it is believed that when these countries stand together, they contribute to a stronger and safer world.